---
description: Minitest conventions and patterns
globs:
  - test/**
---
Testing Conventions (Minitest — NOT RSpec):
- ActiveSupport::TestCase for services/models
- ActiveJob::TestCase for jobs
- ActionDispatch::IntegrationTest for controllers
- NO Mocha gem. Stubs via define_singleton_method on class + ensure restore original Method
- Fake AWS clients as inner classes (FakeBedrockAgentClient, FakeS3Client, etc.)
- parallelize(workers: 1) when tests touch global singletons, AWS clients, or Rails.cache
- ConversationSession: always create! programmatically with unique identifier, never fixtures
- ActionCable: include ActionCable::TestHelper, capture_broadcasts("kb_sync")
- RagController: include Devise::Test::IntegrationHelpers, sign_in users(:one), as: :json
- ENV stubs: save original, set in setup/block, restore in teardown/ensure
- fixtures :all is loaded globally via test_helper.rb (users, bedrock_queries)
- Always verify bin/rails test passes after changes
